Cloves.

13:34.980 --> 13:36.515
The man's amazing.

13:36.515 --> 13:38.484
He has the musical panache
of Leonard Bernstein

13:38.484 --> 13:42.488
and the nose of a Tuscan truffle hog.

13:42.488 --> 13:43.989
You turn my head, sir.

13:43.989 --> 13:45.854
(laughing); Oh, well...
come and meet my father,

13:46.258 --> 13:47.293
Martin Crane.

13:47.293 --> 13:48.994
Well, how lovely to meet you, Martin.

13:48.994 --> 13:49.929
How are you?

13:49.929 --> 13:50.963
Niles. Hello.

13:50.963 --> 13:51.964
Love the tie.

13:51.964 --> 13:52.965
Charvet.

13:52.965 --> 13:56.068
And I'm Daphne , Niles' wife.

13:56.068 --> 13:58.559
No.

14:00.472 --> 14:01.473
We're expecting.

14:01.473 --> 14:04.844
Can't say I was.

14:04.844 --> 14:06.209
How lovely to meet you, Daphne.

14:06.912 --> 14:07.913
Likewise.

14:07.913 --> 14:10.216
Frasier, this apartment is stunning.

14:10.216 --> 14:11.205
Thank you.
The view--

14:11.917 --> 14:12.918
breathtaking.

14:12.918 --> 14:14.220
The art--
perfect.

14:14.220 --> 14:16.916
The chair--
hilarious.

14:19.892 --> 14:21.193
(phone rings) Damn. so sorry.

14:21.193 --> 14:22.888
I have to take this call.

14:23.195 --> 14:24.059
Hello?

14:24.463 --> 14:26.966
Placido!

14:26.966 --> 14:27.967
Placido Domingo?!

14:27.967 --> 14:28.956
Yes.

14:29.468 --> 14:31.527
I'm here with Frasier.

14:31.971 --> 14:34.531
Yes, he's the one I told you about.

14:34.974 --> 14:36.464
Oh, stop.

14:38.444 --> 14:39.502
Oh, oh, yes, uh... in the kitchen

14:39.945 --> 14:42.448
Well, you'll meet him next
month at the concert in Madrid.

14:42.448 --> 14:45.940
Oops, now I've spoiled the surprise.

14:48.020 --> 14:50.921
He's taking me to Madrid!

14:54.927 --> 14:57.259
You just met him last
week. What's going on?

14:57.496 --> 14:58.053
He kissed you.

14:58.497 --> 14:59.999
Well, he's a man of the theater.

14:59.999 --> 15:01.500
He kisses everyone.

15:01.500 --> 15:03.002
It's not like he's the first
gay friend I've ever had.

15:03.002 --> 15:05.027
It's the first one who
thinks you're gay, too.

15:06.972 --> 15:08.340
gay. He does not think I'm

15:08.340 --> 15:12.003
He thinks I'm gay, and I'm
standing next to my pregnant wife.

15:14.179 --> 15:16.515
Have you told him you're straight?

15:16.515 --> 15:20.085
I don't have to. I mean, it's obvious.

15:20.085 --> 15:22.588
We are just friends.
He is not courting me.

15:22.588 --> 15:24.089
Is that a new watch?

15:24.089 --> 15:26.023
so what if it is?

15:28.594 --> 15:31.130
Jewelry. Ooh, he's a keeper.

15:31.130 --> 15:33.999
stop that!

15:33.999 --> 15:35.000
My friendship with Alistair

15:35.000 --> 15:36.502
is the best thing that's
happened to me in months.

15:36.502 --> 15:38.003
I will not have you sully it

15:38.003 --> 15:39.071
by making it out to
be something it's not.

15:39.071 --> 15:40.698
sorry, my angel.

15:43.776 --> 15:45.311
Well, we'd best get to that tailor.

15:45.311 --> 15:46.312
Oh, yes, yes.

15:46.312 --> 15:48.013
We're having new tuxes made

15:48.013 --> 15:50.015
for Alistair's premiere
part y this weekend.

15:50.015 --> 15:51.583
To which you are all invited.

15:51.583 --> 15:52.675
(gasps) ; Thank you.

15:54.620 --> 15:56.622
Will Peter O'Toole be there?

15:56.622 --> 15:58.613
No... and he knows why.

16:01.193 --> 16:03.195
These are amazing.
Where did you get them?

16:03.195 --> 16:04.196
I made them myself.

16:04.196 --> 16:05.698
No...

16:05.698 --> 16:08.200
Is there anything this man can't do?

16:08.200 --> 16:10.566
Time will tell.

16:25.551 --> 16:27.553
Look at this crowd.

16:27.553 --> 16:29.054
It's like a Who's Who

16:29.054 --> 16:33.058
of the creme de la
creme of the upper crust!

16:33.058 --> 16:35.060
Frasier. Alistair.

16:35.060 --> 16:37.563
Your production was a triumph!

16:37.563 --> 16:38.564
Wasn't it?

16:38.564 --> 16:40.054
smile.

16:42.568 --> 16:44.570
Welcome, welcome. Thank you.

16:44.570 --> 16:46.071
There are so many people here

16:46.071 --> 16:47.573
I'm dying for you to meet,

16:47.573 --> 16:49.074
but I have to make a
little announcement first.

16:49.074 --> 16:52.578
Glinka, darling, come and meet Frasier.

16:52.578 --> 16:54.580
Frasier, finally.

16:54.580 --> 16:56.582
Oh, Glinka, it's such
an honor to meet you.

16:56.582 --> 16:59.084
I have all your recordings.

16:59.084 --> 17:02.087
so, I hear that you and
Alistair are quite an item.

17:02.087 --> 17:04.078
Oh, no, no, no, we're
just very good friends.

17:04.589 --> 17:06.580
Oh, yes. Yes, of course.

17:07.092 --> 17:08.093
Everyone,

17:08.093 --> 17:10.596
? . could I have your attention, please

17:10.596 --> 17:14.098
I have to announce that
our very own Nigel Fry

17:14.098 --> 17:16.157
is retiring and giving up his seat

17:16.335 --> 17:18.069
on the Opera board...

17:18.069 --> 17:19.070
(all sigh sadly)

17:19.070 --> 17:22.241
...but I am thrilled
to name as his successor

17:22.241 --> 17:25.243
a tireless supporter
of opera in seattle,

17:25.243 --> 17:27.178
Dr. Frasier Crane.

17:28.313 --> 17:31.316
Oh! Oh, my! Oh, I never dreamed...

17:31.316 --> 17:33.318
Oh, thank you, thank you!

17:33.318 --> 17:35.309
Congratu... Iations.

17:35.821 --> 17:37.823
stunning couple, aren't they?

17:37.823 --> 17:41.122
I'm more stunned by them each day.

17:43.162 --> 17:44.463
Oh, Daph. Quite an honor.

17:44.463 --> 17:46.165
Oh, my God! Isn't it thrilling?

17:46.165 --> 17:47.332
Frasier, can we talk to
you for a moment? Yes.

17:47.332 --> 17:49.300
Do you realize that
every person in this room

17:49.802 --> 17:51.804
thinks that you're Alistair's boyfriend?

17:51.804 --> 17:53.795
 Listen, I can't help it if
people think we're a couple

17:54.306 --> 17:55.808
The point is I'm enjoying myself,

17:55.808 --> 17:56.797
and if you're too jealous
to be happy for me,

17:57.309 --> 17:58.310
then that's your problem.

17:58.310 --> 17:59.311
Jealous?!

17:59.311 --> 18:00.813
Yes, that's right.

18:00.813 --> 18:02.714
All my life I have dreamed

18:02.714 --> 18:04.204
of being half of a power couple,

18:04.716 --> 18:06.707
and I finally am.

18:08.720 --> 18:11.723
Is it perfect? No.

18:11.723 --> 18:14.226
. But it's fun, and
I don't want it to end

18:14.226 --> 18:15.727
Don't you worry at all

18:15.727 --> 18:17.729
that Alistair might be falling for you?

18:17.729 --> 18:19.720
Oh, please. The man has
not even made a move on me,

18:20.232 --> 18:21.233
and do you know why?

18:21.233 --> 18:23.735
Because we are friends.

18:23.735 --> 18:26.238
Famous, fabulous friends.

18:26.238 --> 18:27.739
Oh, uh, Alistair.

18:27.739 --> 18:28.740
Congratulations.

18:28.740 --> 18:30.242
It was a stunning production.

18:30.242 --> 18:31.743
Oh, thank you, Niles.

18:31.743 --> 18:33.745
It must be awfully hard
work putting on an opera.

18:33.745 --> 18:35.747
It is utterly draining.

18:35.747 --> 18:36.748
In fact, when I'm in rehearsals,

18:36.748 --> 18:39.751
I devote every ounce of strength to it.

18:39.751 --> 18:42.254
No exercising, no jogging.

18:42.254 --> 18:44.756
I even abstain from sex.

18:44.756 --> 18:47.247
re. Well, you can ask Frasier he

18:48.694 --> 18:51.686
My poor, dear, patient Frasier.

18:55.200 --> 18:56.702
Care to dance?

18:56.702 --> 18:58.704
I would love to.

18:58.704 --> 19:00.695
Don't go far.

19:08.213 --> 19:11.216
Well, looks like Nigel
won't be the only one

19:11.216 --> 19:13.207
giving up his seat tonight.

19:17.222 --> 19:19.224
I could scratch your eyes out

19:19.224 --> 19:21.715
and not one person here
would find it strange.

19:23.729 --> 19:25.720
I'm sorry.

19:27.232 --> 19:30.724
Damn my fatal allure.

19:32.738 --> 19:34.740
Alistair... when you're
finish with this dance...

19:34.740 --> 19:36.241
Oh, no.

19:36.241 --> 19:37.731
Be my guest.

19:42.247 --> 19:45.250
Frasier, do you have any idea

19:45.250 --> 19:48.253
how sexy you look in that tux?

19:48.253 --> 19:50.244
Yes, I do.

19:52.257 --> 19:53.258
Alistair...

19:53.258 --> 19:55.260
I'm afraid I may have given you

19:55.260 --> 19:56.762
the wrong impression about myself.

19:56.762 --> 19:58.764
You seem nervous. Don't be.

19:58.764 --> 20:01.266
And I want to thank you for waiting.

20:01.266 --> 20:03.268
Oh, no, the waiting was
good. I enjoyed the waiting.

20:03.268 --> 20:05.771
Oh, me too.

20:05.771 --> 20:08.774
How it sharpens the appetite.

20:08.774 --> 20:10.776
How it builds.

20:10.776 --> 20:13.779
The intensity, the heat, the desire.

20:13.779 --> 20:14.780
Can you feel it?

20:14.780 --> 20:17.783
Oh, yes, there it is.

20:17.783 --> 20:19.273
Alistair, um...

20:22.287 --> 20:23.789
Listen, I-I...

20:23.789 --> 20:26.280
I'm afraid I have to
tell you something, uh...

20:27.292 --> 20:29.294
I'm not gay.

20:29.294 --> 20:30.295
Oh, Frasier, please don't tell me

20:30.295 --> 20:32.297
you're still strugglin
g with those issues.

20:32.297 --> 20:35.801
Well, I-I like you so much,
and I love our friendship.

20:35.801 --> 20:38.804
But I'm afraid I can never
really be more than friends.

20:38.804 --> 20:40.305
Would three weeks on Capri

20:40.305 --> 20:43.297
in Bertolucci's villa change your mind?

20:51.316 --> 20:53.318
It's worth a try.

20:53.318 --> 20:54.808
No, no...

20:55.287 --> 20:58.390
No.

20:58.390 --> 21:00.692
It-it wouldn't. I'm sorry.

21:00.692 --> 21:02.694
(sighs) ; Well, then...

21:02.694 --> 21:04.696
I'm so sorry.

21:04.696 --> 21:06.391
so am I.

21:06.698 --> 21:08.400
Could I ask a small favor of you?

21:08.400 --> 21:09.668
Of course. Anything.

21:09.668 --> 21:11.370
Would you mind staying tonight

21:11.370 --> 21:12.671
until my other guests have gone?

21:12.671 --> 21:15.674
I'd hate my friends to
think I'd been jilted.

21:15.674 --> 21:17.376
Of course.

21:17.376 --> 21:18.677
It won't be very late.

21:18.677 --> 21:21.346
Around about 3:00 it's
down to the core crowd,

21:21.346 --> 21:23.348
and we'll all relax and unwind.

21:23.348 --> 21:24.349
It's after midnight, sir.

21:24.349 --> 21:25.684
shall I fire up the hot tub?

21:25.684 --> 21:27.686
Absolutely.

